parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down
and the engine makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft follower can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down
and the high-pressure fuel pump fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump control module can cause the fuel pump to run continuously, resulting in a drained battery and/or a no-start condition, or cause a loss of motive power while the vehicle is in motion, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine damage, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: and the oil warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while in motion, increasing the risk of a crash, injury, and/or damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while in motion
the fuel pump warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle has a strong gasoline smell
fuel leaks onto the rear seats
the vehicle has a sudden loss of power on city streets or on the highway
the fuel pump is hot under the rear passenger seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall remedies for the fuel system can lead to continued risk of fuel pump failure, stalling, and loss of power, increasing the risk of a crash, injury, and/or damage to property.
symptoms: The vehicle is under recall for the fuel pump module
but the parts to do the repair are unavailable
the vehicle stalls or loses power while in motion
the fuel pump warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle has a strong gasoline smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure (Fuel Pump, High Pressure Fuel Pump, and Fuel Rail/System Pressure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience poor acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Camshaft and High Pressure Fuel Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Camshaft and high pressure fuel pump failure can cause the engine to stall, lose power, or experience poor acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Intake manifold and turbocharger failure can cause the engine to lose power, experience poor acceleration, and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Delays and Parts Unavailability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs and unavailability of parts can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: as this is a service-related issue.
